<fw type="curatorial">25</fw>

<fw type="letterhead">

EDITORIAL∙DEPARTMENT
<lb/>
THE CENTURY∙MAGAZINE
<lb/>
UNION∙SQUARE∙NEW∙YORK   
<lb/>

<hi rend="italics">
R. W. GILDER, EDITOR
<lb/> 
R. U. JOHNSON, ASSOCIATE EDITOR
<lb/>
C. C. BUEL, ASSISTANT EDITOR
</hi>
</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>May 3, 1909</dateline>

<salute>Mr. John G. Neihardt</salute>

<salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
</opener>
<p>I trust that you will not consider it presuming when I ask you to do me the very great favor of letting me know when "Prayer for Pain" is published &#8212; for I 

<pb facs="nei.j4a.1.25b"/>

feel sure that it will be published and I deeply regret that it is not to be in the <title>Century</title>.</p>

<p>The poem has made a profound impression upon me, and has haunted me ever since I first read it so I should like to own it some day. It is such a glorious fighting song!</p>

<p>I shall be so much obliged to you.</p>
<closer>

<salute>Sincerely</salute>

<signed>H. C. Bliss (first reader)</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
